      <mxCell id="s_44" value="This diagram shows the backend architecture for a real-time multiplayer game. Players connect via WebSocket for low-latency gameplay. All game events flow through Kafka for async processing by downstream services. Player data, rankings, and telemetry are stored in purpose-built databases." style="shape=document;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;boundedLbl=1;backgroundOutline=1;size=0.27;fillColor=#F8FAFC;strokeColor=#CBD5E1;fontColor=#555555;fontSize=11;fontStyle=2;align=left;verticalAlign=top;shape=document;" vertex="1" parent="l_3">
